Monday, May 26, 2025


Beaufort, NC is a coastal town in eastern North Carolina with a humid subtropical climate characterized by long, hot summers and short, cool winters. It is located on the Beaufort Inlet with barrier islands and the Atlantic Ocean to the south, the southern end of the North Carolina Outer Banks to the east, and the tidal Newport River to the west. The current NOAA weather station has been installed on a pier at the Duke University Marine Laboratory on Pivers Island since June 1990.
